Satjiv S. Chahil: Executive Profile & Biography - Bloomberg









































  





















































































July 22, 2017 3:39 AM ET
Communications Equipment

Company Overview of Alcatel-Lucent Canada Inc.



SnapshotPeople 




OverviewBoard MembersCommittees



Executive Profile
Satjiv S. Chahil  Executive Vice President - Marketing, Alcatel-Lucent Canada Inc.AgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 2 Board Members in 2 different organizations across 6 different industries.See Board Relationships66--
Background

		Mr. Satjiv S. Chahil served as a Vice President of PC Division at Hewlett-Packard Company. Mr. Chahil has a reputation for creating and implementing impactful marketing campaigns to achieve dramatic results consistent with the goals of high-tech corporations. He served as Senior Vice President of Marketing of Personal Systems Group at Hewlett-Packard Company since September 8, 2005. He served as Chief Marketing Officer of Palm Ventures, the venture capital investment ... arm of Palm, Inc. Prior to Hewlett-Packard, he served as Interim Chief Operating Officer of Palm Solutions (a division of Palm, Inc.) from March 2001 to July 2001 and Chief Marketing Officer of Palm, Inc. from March 2000 to June 2002. Prior to that, he served as the Chief Marketing Officer and Executive Vice President of Marketing for Alcatel-Lucent Canada Inc. (Alternatively known as Newbridge Networks Corp.), from February 1999 to March 2000, which was acquired by Alcatel in May 2000. He joined Alcatel Canada, Inc. in February 1999. Prior to that, Mr. Chahil served as President of Chahil.com, a marketing consulting organization based in California's Silicon Valley, since May 1997. From July 1997 to February 1999, he served as the Digital Convergence Advisor of Sony Electronics, Inc., a U.S. business unit of Sony Corporation focused on the Manufacture, Sale and Marketing of consumer and professional audio and video equipment and other electronic components. He also served as a Consultant to Sony Corporation, from May 1997 to March 2000. From September 1988 to February 1997, Mr. Chahil served in various capacities, including Senior Vice President of Worldwide Marketing and the Founding General Manager of the New Media, Internet and Entertainment division, at Apple Computer. He was responsible for Worldwide Marketing and Corporate Communications. Prior to that, from September 1976 to September 1988, Mr. Chahil held various international sales, marketing and general management positions at IBM and Xerox. He was Co-Founder of Mobile Digital Media Inc. He has over 30 years of high-tech marketing experience gained at IBM, Xerox, Apple and Sony. He led the team that launched Sony's convergence strategy, including VAIO notebooks, digital photography/imaging and e-business. His creativity was key to Sony rapidly becoming a market leader in each of these new business categories. He served as Head of Sales and Marketing and Chairman of Palm Ventures. He joined HP from Palm, where he served as an Advisor to the Chairman since June 2002. He served as the Chairman of Mobile Digital Media, a Palm spin-off. Mr. Chahil served as the Chairman of the Board of Quickoffice, Inc. He has been an Independent Director of Universal Electronics Inc. since August 19, 2002. He has been a Trustee of The American India Foundation since October 2012. He served as a Director of TrueContext Corporation and Quickoffice, Inc. He served as a Director of ACCESS Systems Americas, Inc. from May 2002 to October 28, 2004. He served as a Director of Orb Networks Inc., ProntoForms Corporation and Palm Ventures. He serves on the Millenium Council of the American Film Institute. He also initiated some of the IT industry's first cross-industry co-branding initiatives, including campaigns with BMW and two Hollywood studios. He has strong ties to the creative communities in the publishing, advertising, film and music industries. He has been a featured speaker at global technology conferences, as well as at Harvard, Stanford and The Sorbonne. Mr. Chahil earned a Master's Degree in Business from American Thunderbird, The Garvin School of International Management, Arizona, USA and also holds a Bachelor of Commerce Degree from Punjab University in Chandigarh, India.Read Full Background




